<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 4:53AM EDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Clay County
through 530 AM EDT...
At 452 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Nantahala Lake, or 8 miles east of Hayesville, moving
southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Nantahala Lake, Shooting Creek and Tusquitee.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
